data.enText: not done, seen, happening, etc. very often

data.chText: 罕见的疾病 / 事件；难得一见的事物
四月份就这样炎热是极其罕见的。
data.enText: It's extremely rare for it to be this hot in April.

data.chText: 这样忠心耿耿，在今天非常少见。
data.enText: It is rare to find such loyalty these days.

data.chText: 彼此难得相见，他还几乎不敢跟她说话。
data.enText: On the rare occasions when they met he hardly even dared speak to her.

data.chText: 成为这所学院的研究员是极大的荣誉。
data.enText: It was a rare (= very great) honour to be made a fellow of the college.
existing only in small numbers and therefore valuable or interesting

data.chText: 珍贵的书 / 硬币 / 邮票

data.enText: cooked for only a short time so that the inside is still red

example: rare patches of green in the desert

tr: especially superlative or extreme of its kind
example: what is so rare as a day in June"-J.R.Lowel
she was kind to an uncommon degree
lightheaded from the rarefied mountain air

value.def: Something that is rare is not common and is therefore interesting or valuable.

example.ex: ...the black-necked crane, one of the rarest species in the world...
example.tran: 黑颈鹤，世界最稀有的物种之一

example.ex: Do you want to know about a particular rare stamp or rare stamps in general?
example.tran: 你是想了解某一种珍稀邮票还是想了解珍稀邮票的整体概念？

value.def: An event or situation that is rare does not occur very often.

example.ex: ...on those rare occasions when he did eat alone...
example.tran: 在那些极其少见的、他的确单独吃饭的时候

example.ex: Heart attacks were extremely rare in babies, he said...
example.tran: 婴儿极少有心脏病发作的情况，他说。

example.ex: It's apparently rare for anyone to have two legs the same length...
example.tran: 显然，一个人两条腿的长度完全相同的情况是很少见的。

example.ex: I think it's very rare to have big families nowadays.
example.tran: 我想，如今大家庭已经很少见了。

value.def: You use rare to emphasize an extremely good or remarkable quality.

example.ex: Ferris has a rare ability to record her observations on paper...
example.tran: 费里斯具备把自己的观察结果记录下来的超强能力。

example.ex: It was a rare pleasure to see him in action.
...a leader of rare strength and instinct.
example.tran: 拥有杰出才干和天赋的领导

value.def: Meat that is rare is cooked very lightly so that the inside is still red.

example.ex: Thick tuna steaks are eaten rare, like beef...
example.tran: 像牛肉一样，厚的金枪鱼排做到半熟即可食用。

example.ex: Waiter, I specifically asked for this steak rare.
example.tran: 服务员，我特别强调了这块牛排要做得嫩些。
